{"id":413366845,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"2 years, 11 months","timestamp":1603720240,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"52 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/413366845/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"37.6 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        vector<int> tree;\n        helper(root, tree);\n        \n        for (int i=0; i<tree.size()-1; i++) {\n            for (int j=i+1; j<tree.size(); j++) {\n                if (tree[i] + tree[j] == k)\n                    return true;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return false;\n    }\n    \n    void helper(TreeNode* root, vector<int>& tree) {\n        if (root == NULL)\n            return;\n        \n        tree.push_back(root->val);\n        helper(root->left, tree);\n        helper(root->right, tree);     \n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
